<h1>OPI Spanish Exam Preparation</h1><p>&nbsp;Casa Xelajú offers personalized OPI Spanish Test Preparation for students and professionals seeking to excel in the Oral Proficiency Interview (OPI). Their program provides one-on-one instruction with certified Spanish teachers, available both in-person in Quetzaltenango, Guatemala, and online via Skype. The course is fully aligned with ACTFL and CEFR standards, offering practice sessions that simulate real OPI exam conditions to build fluency, accuracy, and confidence. It is ideal for educators, healthcare professionals, and anyone needing official speaking proficiency certification.</p><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.casaxelaju.com/opi-spanish-test-preparation/" ><img border="0" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEggkuxnCEbB4W8E7QxSevKVCZ2F30rizvqZsvTFkB80dSO-IjgdGyOAjX71iclVdw1zgvzbc4eubLdmquGMgFjXCPoVmlWVQSzsm4os80v3wAlArGeBFSvmCFps8YcjK0hyphenhyphen0Jixh82DuLTaNyFmEncm2PpJksxwxjcd7BgD2-lWqfPahwRs7iZzhs1cVb9U/s16000/best-spanish-school-quetzaltenango-guatemala-700x525.jpg-300x225.webp" /></a></div>
<p>&nbsp;The OPI Spanish Test Preparation program focuses on improving speaking skills, pronunciation, and overall conversational confidence. Casa Xelajú ensures students are well-prepared through immersive lessons, real test simulations, and individualized attention from experienced native instructors. The OPI, originally created by the U.S. Foreign Service Institute and refined by ACTFL, evaluates functional speaking ability and is used by bilingual teachers, school districts, and professionals to assess oral proficiency for employment or certification.</p><iframe width="100%" height="550" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/XzIMal36tQU" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<p>&nbsp;Students benefit from a comprehensive approach that combines daily one-on-one instruction with cultural immersion. Those attending in Guatemala stay with local host families, enjoy three meals a day, and participate in three to four social and cultural activities per week. For those unable to travel, online preparation via Skype provides the same quality instruction. Tuition for the in-person program, which includes 25 hours of instruction per week, homestay, meals, and cultural activities, is $310 per week. Online classes offer flexible scheduling and one-on-one attention for students worldwide.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Casa Xelajú has a long history of academic excellence, with over 36 Spanish courses including preparation for the DELE, Praxis II, BCLAD, TOPT, FSI, SAT II, CLEP, and other proficiency exams. Their teachers have extensive experience and formal training in test preparation. The program has helped numerous students achieve their OPI goals, with many testimonials confirming the effectiveness of the personalized instruction. Graduates report significant improvement in fluency and confidence, enabling them to reach advanced levels and pursue professional or academic goals in Spanish-speaking environments.</p><iframe width="100%" height="550" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/7MP_-IIjalM" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<p>&nbsp;With over 35 years of teaching experience and more than 12,000 former students, Casa Xelajú is fully licensed by the Guatemalan Secretary of Education. Their OPI Spanish Test Preparation equips students with the skills to pass the exam, while also fostering practical language abilities applicable in professional, educational, and cultural settings. Students receive progress evaluations and practice assessments to monitor readiness, ensuring that every participant is fully prepared for the official ACTFL OPI exam.</p>
